<emphasis box="[729,874,1543,1569]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="68">Hermundura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has 17 valid species. From Western Atlantic, three species were recorded namely 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Berkeley &amp; Berkeley" baseAuthorityYear="1941" box="[490,599,1579,1605]" class="Polychaeta" family="Pilargidae" genus="Hermundura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="12" pageNumber="68" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="fauveli">
<emphasis box="[490,599,1579,1605]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="68">H. fauveli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, from 
<collectingRegion box="[672,802,1579,1605]" country="United States of America" name="Mississippi" pageId="12" pageNumber="68">Mississippi</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[813,867,1580,1606]" name="United States of America" pageId="12" pageNumber="68">USA</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Hartman, O." box="[880,1046,1580,1606]" pageId="12" pageNumber="68" pagination="483 - 523" refId="ref13641" refString="Hartman, O. (1947) Polychaetous annelids. Part VIII. Pilargidae. Allan Hancock Pacific Expeditions, 10 (5),, 483 - 523." type="journal article" year="1947">Hartman 1947</bibRefCitation>
